      },
      "date": "2013-05-06 15:28:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nTwo minor issues:\n- in osd_check_lma() there is still a -EINVAL in the CERROR() that should be -ESTALE. It would be better to move the rc assignment before the CERROR() and then just use rc as the parameter. \n- there is a prototype declaration for osd_object_find(), but it doesn't look like it is used, and in any case it is unsafe to declare function prototypes in .c files because this can cause bugs if the function ever changes. If this is really needed, put it into a header like osd_internal.h.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
