      "message": "Patch Set 9: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nBasically, it is OK for me.\n\nJust one concern about the repeated logic for LMA verification. As you can see, there are two branches inside osd_fid_lookup(): osd_iget() and osd_iget_verify(), for the later case, it has already get LMA, and verified the FID-in-LMA. On the other hand, osd_check_lma() after the osd_fid_lookup() get the LMA and verify similar things again.\n\nSo if possible, please adjust the code, and drop those redundant logic.\n\nThanks.",
